    "problemStatement": "Given two strings S1 and S2, find the longest common substring between them.\n\nA substring means:\n\ncontinuous characters\n\nmust appear exactly as-is in both strings\n\nReturn:\n\nthe longest common substring\n\nif more than one substring has the same length, return the one that appears first in S1\n\nif no common substring exists, return -1\n\n✔ Example\n\nInput:\n\nabcdef\nzabcfxy\n\n\nCommon substrings are:\na, ab, abc, bc, bcd, cde\n\nLongest = abc\n\nOutput:\nabc",
